^^^&USER LICENSE RECOGNITION\\\&
.BLANK 2
^ALL USER LICENSE CHECKS WILL BE CONTROLLED BY A SINGLE
ROUTINE WITHIN ^^LMR\\ WHICH WILL BE PASSED THE LICENSE
REQUIRED TO BE CHECKED.
  ^THIS ROUTINE WILL THEN CHECK THIS AGAINST THE
LICENSE CURRENTLY HELD BY THE USER AND WILL RETURN A VALUE OF
^^TRUE\\ IF THE USER HAS SUFFICIENT LICENSE TO PERFORM THE FUNCTION.
^IF THE USER'S LICENSE IS LESS THAN REQUIRED, THE ROUTINE WILL 
INFORM THE USER WHAT ADDITIONAL LICENSE IS REQUIRED AND RETURN THE
VALUE  ^^FALSE\\.  ^THE USER MAY THEN SELECT TO USE THE
.INDEX ^^SET LICENSE\\
^^SET LICENSE\\ COMMAND TO OBTAIN THE LICENSE REQUIRED
IF HE CAN DO SO OR HE MAY SELECT TO NOT EXECUTE THE COMMAND
PREVIOUSLY SELECTED.
.PARAGRAPH
^USER LICENSE CHECKS WILL BE MADE PRIOR TO THE ACCEPTANCE OF
THE COMMAND DIRECTIVE SINCE ALL OPERATIONS PERFORMED BY ^^LMR\\
WILL USE THE LICENSE GIVEN TO THE PROGRAM RATHER THAN THE USER.
^THE
.INDEX ^^SET\\
^^SET\\ DIRECTIVE MAY BE USED TO ALTER THE LICENSE REQUIRED BY ^^LMR\\
TO EXECUTE A DIRECTIVE BY STATING THE FOLLOWING:
.BLANK 1
^^SET [(DIRECTIVE) (/SWITCH)] [NEW LICENSE]\\
.BLANK 1
^THE CURRENTLY REQUIRED LICENSE WILL BE PRINTED.  ^THE USER WILL BE
REQUIRED TO HAVE THE MAXIMUM OR COMPOSITE LICENSE SET 
 OLD AND NEW LICENSE REQUIREMENT OFTHE DIRECTIVE BEING
CHANGED.  ^IN ADDITION, ^^LMR\\ WILL REQUIRE THAT THE USER HAVE 
.INDEX ^^WF\\
^^WF\\ (^WRITE ^FILES) LICENSE SET IN ORDER TO EXECUTE THIS DIRECTIVE.
.PARAGRAPH
^THE CONCEPT OF USER LICENSE VALIDATION AND CHECKING IS OF UTMOST
IMPORTANCE
SINCE ^^LMR\\ WILL BE RUNNING WITH SUFFICIENT
LICENSE TO COMPLETELY MODIFY THE RUNNING SYSTEM.  ^IT IS
IMPERATIVE THAT UNAUTHORIZED PERSONNEL NOT BE ABLE TO
ACCOMPLISH THIS FEAT.
^CONSEQUENTLY, ^^LMR\\ WILL MAKE AN INITIAL CHECK FOR ^^TYMSHARE\\
AND ^^ACCOUNT SUPERVISOR\\ LICENSE BEFORE PERMITTING THE USER
ACCESS TO THE PROGRAM.
